19.7599 	EXP 	str_keyInst_pract: text = 'In this task, we will measure the speed with which you are\nable to detect two dots.\n\nThe dots can appear at the top or at the bottom of the\nscreen, like this ":" or like this ".."\n\nYour job is to indicate which orientation the dots are in by\npressing the correspondingly labelled button.\n\nEach trial will begin with a cross (+) in the middle of the\nscreen.  You should focus your attention on that cross.\n\nVery soon after the cross disappears, two faces will flash\nup on the screen, one at the top and one at the bottom. The\ndots will appear after.\n\nAs soon as you see the dots you should indicate which\norientation they are in by pressing the ":" button or the\n".." button as quickly and accurately as you can.\n\nPlease use your index fingers, and keep them on the two\nresponse buttons throughout the task.\n\nYou will be able to respond to the dots faster if you always\nfocus your attention on the cross that begins each trial.\n\nBoth accuracy and speed are important.\n\nPlease inform the researcher if you are ready to continue.\n\n\n[Researcher: Press SPACE BAR to begin key map check]'
